.Dd December 2025
.Dt CC 7
.Os Fedora
.Sh NAME
.Nm cc
.Nd Conventional Commits & Description Guidelines
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm <type> Ns Op (scope) Ns Op ! :
.Ar <description>
.Sh DESCRIPTION
A convention for commit messages to create a machine-readable history.
.Sh TYPES
.Bl -tag -width "refactor" -compact
.It Ic feat
New feature (MINOR)
.It Ic fix
Bug fix (PATCH)
.It Ic perf
Performance improvement
.It Ic refactor
Code change (neither fix nor feature)
.It Ic docs
Documentation only
.It Ic style
Formatting, missing semi-colons, etc.
.It Ic build
Build system/dependencies
.It Ic ci
CI configuration
.It Ic test
Adding/fixing tests
.It Ic chore
Maintenance tasks
.El
.Sh DESCRIPTION GUIDELINES
Follow these rules for the 
.Ar <description>
field to ensure precision:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Sy Imperative Mood :
Use "add" instead of "added" or "adds". (Matches git's own generated messages).
.It
.Sy Case :
Start with lowercase (unless starting with a proper noun).
.It
.Sy Length :
Keep under 50 characters.
.It
.Sy Punctuation :
Do not end with a period.
.It
.Sy Content :
Summarize
.Em what
the change does, not
.Em how
it was done.
.El
.Sh BREAKING CHANGES
Indicated by
.Ic !
after type/scope. Triggers a
.Ic MAJOR
version bump.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Dl fix(parser): resolve overflow in hex reader
.Dl feat(api)!: remove deprecated endpoints
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Lk https://www.conventionalcommits.org
